ThinkPart(
    type='think',
    think='Let me now try to understand what the PR actually changed. Since I ca
n\'t get the git diff, I need to make reasonable inferences based on what I see 
in the current branch vs what the main branch likely had.\n\nFrom the main branc
h reflog, the last commit was "docs: fix matching Redis cache type and Haversine
SQL in PRD/exec-plan" which suggests main had the PRD and exec-plan documents bu
t not much implementation code.\n\nThis PR branch has:\n- Full NestJS API with a
uth, blocks, reports, content-moderation, admin, health modules\n- Database migr
ation and entities\n- Mobile app with generated models\n- Design system with Wid
getbook\n- Admin app with login and dashboard\n- BDD tests\n- CI pipeline\n- Ope
nAPI contracts\n- Scripts for type generation, docs check, etc.\n\nSo this PR is
basically the infrastructure bootstrap + auth implementation. Given the branch n
ame `feat/issue-1`, this is likely the very first feature implementation.\n\nNow
let me identify issues:\n\n**1. Full-chain integrity:**\n- DB: ✅ Migration exis
ts, entities exist\n- API: ✅ Auth controller/service exists, but it\'s incomple
te (register is just a stub, login is just a stub, no JWT implementation, no ref
resh, no logout, no Redis integration for SMS codes or tokens)\n- Mobile: ❌ No 
BLoC, no login page, no secure storage, no interceptor - only main.dart with a s
tub UI and generated models\n- According to PRD/exec plan, mobile should have: A
uth BLoC, login page, secure storage, Dio interceptor\n\n**2. Spec compliance:**
\n- The auth controller has `POST /auth/register` but PRD says register/login sh
ould be merged to `POST /auth/login`\n- The auth.yaml contract defines `POST /ap
i/v1/auth/login` with `phone` and `sms_code`, but the actual `AuthController` ha
s separate `register` and `login` endpoints that don\'t match the contract\n- `R
egisterDto` only has `phone` and `birth_date` - missing `sms_code`, and no valid
ation decorators (class-validator)\n- No JWT Guard exists (`apps/api/src/common/
guards/jwt-auth.guard.ts` is referenced in docs but doesn\'t exist)\n- NestJS ma
in.ts uses `AllExceptionsFilter` but it references `request.user?.userId` - howe
ver there\'s no JWT guard to set `request.user`\n- Mobile is missing the BLoC, l
ogin page, secure storage, interceptor\n- `calculateAge` has a bug: `birthMonth 
= 2` comment says March (0-indexed), but `birthMonth` is 0-indexed, so February 
is month 1. If birthDay is Feb 29 and it\'s not a leap year, they set `birthMont
h = 2` (March) and `birthDay = 1` (March 1). This seems correct actually.\n\nWai
t, looking more carefully at `calculateAge`:\n```typescript\nif (birthMonth === 
1 && birthDay === 29) {\n  const isLeapYear = ...\n  if (!isLeapYear(now.getUTCF
ullYear())) {\n    birthMonth = 2; // March (0-indexed)\n    birthDay = 1;\n  }\
n}\n```\nYes, this is correct. Feb = 1, March = 2 in 0-indexed.\n\n**3. Contract
consistency:**\n- `auth.yaml` defines `LoginResponse` with `access_token`, `refr
esh_token`, `expires_in`, `user_id` (optional)\n- But the actual API `AuthContro
ller.login()` returns `{ access_token, refresh_token, expires_in, user_id }` whi
ch matches\n- However, `auth.yaml` defines `POST /auth/login` with `phone` and `
sms_code`, but `AuthController.register()` takes `phone` and `birth_date` - comp
letely different!\n- `auth.yaml` defines `POST /auth/refresh` but `AuthControlle
r` doesn\'t implement it\n- The generated types exist for auth.yaml, but the API
doesn\'t actually implement what the contract says\n- Missing `is_new_user` in L
oginResponse (both in YAML and generated types, and in API stub)\n\n**4. Test co
verage:**\n- `auth.service.spec.ts` exists but only tests register with age chec
k\n- No tests for login, refresh, logout, SMS validation, token generation\n- No
mobile tests\n- BDD step definitions exist but are all empty stubs\n- `age-calcu
lator.spec.ts` has good coverage for edge cases\n\n**5. Documentation sync:**\n-
`docs/modules/auth.md` references `apps/mobile/lib/presentation/blocs/auth/` whi
ch doesn\'t exist\n- Need to check if `docs/modules/INDEX.md` includes auth modu
